# Gremyachinsk, Republic of Buryatia

}}
Gremyachinsk () is a rural locality (a selo) in Pribaykalsky District, Republic of Buryatia, Russia. The population was 846 as of 2010. There are 21 streets.
Geography
Gremyachinsk is located 88&nbsp;km north of Turuntayevo (the district's administrative centre) by road. Kotokel is the nearest rural locality.
